		    Version 1·0  ©1997 Dan Rhodes

This is a program to remove comments from header files and other source
code.  Using it on your include directories can save a considerable amount
of hard disk space, and also make your programs compile faster.

Blank lines and white space at the end of lines are also removed.

HeadShrink should work on any Amiga (but that doesn't mean it will ;-)

